						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">SMB3 has levels up to 27 metatiles tall</div>
<br />
<br />(Please excuse some slight off-topicness)
<br />
<br />Hey, I recognize that number! That's how high vertical levels are in Super Mario World. I've always found that choice quite odd, seeing as it's such an uneven number and makes X/Y coordinate to RAM address calculations less efficient.
<br />
<br />...and now you tell me that SMB3 has the same odd level height?
<br />
<br />Why? What's so special about the number 27? Did they pick a random number and simply decided to stick with it, or is there some brilliant reason I'm missing here?</div>

