				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Smallhacker wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why? What's so special about the number 27? Did they pick a random number and simply decided to stick with it, or is there some brilliant reason I'm missing here?</div>
<br />The NES has 2 name tables, and each one is 30 tiles (240 pixels) tall. In SMB3 they are arranged one on top of the other for a total of 60 tiles. The bottommost 6 rows are used for the status bar, which means that 54 are free for the level, enough for 27 metatiles.
<br />
<br />On the SNES I'm not sure. I don't think background maps are 30 tiles tall on the SNES, so I see no reason for them to stick with that limitation. Maybe that game was built on top of SM3, and they simply never changed that aspect of the engine.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

